🛰️ G-NOV SENTINEL
Next-Gen Multimodal AI-Ops Agent for Autonomous Workspace Governance

G-Nov Sentinel is a sovereign AI entity built for the Gemini Live Agent Challenge. It moves beyond simple text-in/text-out interactions by utilizing real-time Audio & Visual Telemetry to navigate, monitor, and automate complex UI workflows.

🚀 Project Overview
Category: UI Navigator / Live Agent

Core Tech: Gemini 3 Flash, Google GenAI SDK, Socket.io

Deployment: Google Cloud Platform (GCP)

🛡️ Key Features
Neural Voice Link: Natural language interaction with a deep-tactical voice response system.

Visual Telemetry (Cyber-Scan): Real-time screen analysis to identify UI bugs and code anomalies.

Ghost-Fix Mapping: High-precision coordinate overlay for intercepted system errors.

Automated Workspace (In-Dev): Autonomous tab orchestration and data injection into tactical drafts.

🏗️ System Architecture
The Sentinel operates on a duplex communication layer between the Browser and Google Cloud.

Input Layer: Captures real-time Voice (Mic) and Visuals (Screen/Camera).

Neural Layer: Processes multimodal frames via Gemini 3 Flash.

Execution Layer: Python/Flask backend hosted on GCP triggers system-level UI actions.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Models: Google Gemini 3 Flash (Multimodal)

Backend: Python 3.10, Flask-SocketIO, Eventlet

Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (3D Neural Core), JavaScript (ES6)

Cloud: Google Cloud Engine, Google Cloud Shell, Vertex AI

