🛡️ G-NOV SENTINEL: Multimodal AI-Ops Engine
Category: UI Navigator

Core Brain: Google Gemini 3 Flash

Deployment: Google Cloud Platform (GCP)

🚀 Overview
G-NOV SENTINEL is an autonomous UI Navigator designed to eliminate visual blindness in DevOps. By leveraging the multimodal capabilities of Gemini 3 Flash, Sentinel can see the user's interface, hear vocal commands, and execute system actions in real-time.

🛠️ Technical Architecture
We use a real-time event-driven pipeline:

Frontend: 3D Kinetic Dashboard (HTML5/CSS3) with Socket.io streaming.

Backend: Python Flask-SocketIO engine hosted on Google Cloud Run.

Intelligence: Gemini 3 Flash via Vertex AI for visual telemetry analysis and Ghost-Fix coordinate mapping.

[Yahan mere wale Diagram ka link ya image daal dena]

✨ Key Features
Visual Telemetry: Real-time screen analysis to detect UI regressions.

Multimodal Intent Parsing: Combining voice and vision to understand complex user goals.

Ghost-Fix Navigation: Autonomous execution of UI tasks using identified coordinates.

Neural Archives: Session persistence and mission logging.

🏗️ Automated Cloud Deployment
Sentinel is built for the cloud. We automate our deployment using Google Cloud Build and custom shell scripts.

Containerization: Docker/GCR.

Serverless Execution: Google Cloud Run.

Infrastructure-as-Code: Automated via deploy.sh.

